Department of Justice to announce findings of investigation into Cleveland Police
The Justice Department is expected to announce the findings of a 20-month investigation into the Cleveland Police Department's use of deadly force, training, discipline, recruitment, and relations with minority communities. The news comes less than two weeks after a Cleveland Police officer shot and killed  , a black 12-year-old who was carrying an airsoft gun — a toy — at the time of his death. Watch the Department of Justice's press conference here, courtesy of Cleveland news station  :   